bug.short_desc: default notify position makes it hard to change volume
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1235583 xfce-notify-problem.ogv
Description of problem: By default if I am using xfce 4, the notification comes out in top right of the screen, regardless of what's behind. So if volume is in the same position, it makes hard to adjust volume control
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): Fedora 25 XFCE xfce4-notifyd-0.3.4-1.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install Fedora XFCE and log in 2. Adjust volume from the volume icon 3.
Actual results: Volume adjust area are mostly covered by notification
Expected results: Notify don't cover the volume control
Additional info: See the attached ogv video if the steps is not clear enough for you. I remember some newer version of Fedora 24 XFCE also have this issue. And currently the workaround is simple, but not user-friendly enough, either
run xfce4-notifyd-config and change the Default Position to somewhere else, or
move the volume control from the default position to somewhere else.
But I hope there is a much user-friendly default settings for users.

Well, I am not sure if other locations are too much better... each has tradeoffs.
This might be a good discussion for the fedora-xfce list. Would you be willing to bring it up there? Or if not, I can do so...

Fine, I just send it to the list
https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/xfce@lists.fedoraproject.org/thread/GUHF5SZWCDYG5KAMJOZ575MFPOPYDSRT/
